By the way the SettingMgr class is a singleton, it can look intimidating but it's really easy to use:
settings.set("foo.bar.baz.mysetting", 123);
console.log(settings.get("foo.bar.baz.mysetting"));

If will convert the path to a JSON format and store it in storage.local (you can change that to storage.sync if you prefer)
It support migration method if you need the settings to be re-organized for an update. You would add a check for a version of whatever and add your migration logic in there.
It also support default settings, a value where if no setting exist, it will default to.
